You are building a "Corporate Website Factory": a reusable .NET Core 10 MVC starter kit that I will publish per client. After publishing, the client can update the content via an admin panel. This is NOT a full CMS and MUST NOT include a drag-drop page builder or a generic content engine.

========================
1) TECH STACK (STRICT)
========================
- .NET Core 10 MVC (preview acceptable)
- EF Core
- SQLite
- Razor Views
- Bootstrap 5 + clean light corporate theme (single theme)
- Admin panel language: Turkish only
- Public site language: TR + EN
- No authentication required for now, but architecture must allow adding it later easily (e.g. a single filter/attribute or middleware gate can be added later).

No deployment/IIS steps.

========================
2) REPO STRUCTURE (MANDATORY)
========================
Create a solution named `CorporateWebsiteFactory` with projects:
- CorporateWebsiteFactory.Web (MVC)
- CorporateWebsiteFactory.Data (EF Core, Entities, DbContext, Migrations, Seed)

Folder structure:
CorporateWebsiteFactory.Web
- Areas/Admin/Controllers
- Areas/Admin/Views
- Areas/Admin/ViewModels
- Controllers
- Views
- Services
- Middlewares
- wwwroot/cdn/img/blog
- wwwroot/cdn/img/product
- wwwroot/cdn/img/portfolio
- wwwroot/assets (css/js)

CorporateWebsiteFactory.Data
- Entities
- Enums
- AppDbContext.cs
- Seed/DbSeeder.cs
- Migrations

========================
3) MULTI LANGUAGE (STRICT)
========================
- Languages: `tr`, `en`
- URL prefix: `/tr/...` and `/en/...`
- Implement a Language middleware or route constraint ensuring only tr/en accepted.
- Add language switcher to the public layout.
- Implement hreflang tags for corresponding TR/EN pages.
- Content tables: implement translation pairing with:
  - ContentGroupId (GUID)
  - Language (string: tr|en)

========================
4) CONTENT MODEL (CONTROLLED, NOT CMS)
========================
I want fixed corporate pages and structured content fields so the site cannot be broken by clients.

Entities (all translatable via ContentGroupId+Language where applicable):
A) SiteSettings (not translatable, or optionally per language):
- SiteName
- LogoPath
- FaviconPath
- FooterText
- GoogleAnalyticsId (or script)
- GoogleTagManagerId (or script)
- DefaultMetaTitle, DefaultMetaDescription
- Social links

B) MenuItem (per language)
- Title, Url, ParentId, DisplayOrder, IsVisible

C) Fixed pages as structured entities (per language):
- HomePageContent:
  - HeroTitle, HeroSubtitle, HeroImagePath
  - Section1Title, Section1Html
  - Section2Title, Section2Html
  - CTA_Title, CTA_Text, CTA_ButtonText, CTA_ButtonUrl
- AboutPageContent:
  - Title, BodyHtml, ImagePath
- ServicesPageContent:
  - Title, IntroHtml
- ContactPageContent:
  - Title, IntroHtml
  - Address, Phone, Email, MapEmbedHtml
- ReferencesPageContent:
  - Title, IntroHtml
- FaqPageContent:
  - Title, IntroHtml
(These are fixed templates; do not implement a generic Page table.)

D) Blog
- BlogPost (translatable)
  - Title, Slug, Summary, BodyHtml, FeaturedImagePath
  - CategoryId
  - Status: Draft/Review/Published
  - PublishAt nullable
  - SEO fields (see below)
- BlogCategory (translatable)
  - Name, Slug, DisplayOrder

E) Product (catalog only)
- ProductItem (translatable)
  - Title, Slug, Summary, BodyHtml, FeaturedImagePath
  - CategoryId
  - Status + PublishAt
  - SEO fields
- ProductCategory (translatable)

F) Portfolio
- PortfolioItem (translatable)
  - Title, Slug, Summary, BodyHtml
  - CategoryId
  - FeaturedImagePath
  - GalleryImages (separate table PortfolioImage: Id, PortfolioItemId, ImagePath, DisplayOrder)
  - Status + PublishAt
  - SEO fields
- PortfolioCategory (translatable)

G) Reference items (optional: either translatable or single language; choose consistent approach)
- ReferenceItem:
  - Name, LogoPath, WebsiteUrl, DisplayOrder, IsVisible

H) FAQ Items (translatable)
- FaqItem:
  - Question, AnswerHtml, DisplayOrder, IsVisible

I) Redirects (not translatable)
- RedirectRule:
  - OldPath, NewPath, StatusCode (301/302), IsActive

J) Contact Form Submissions (not translatable)
- ContactSubmission:
  - Name, Email, Message, CreatedAt

Common fields for translatable content types:
- Id (GUID)
- ContentGroupId (GUID)
- Language (tr|en)
- Slug (unique per Language per entity type)
- CreatedAt, UpdatedAt
- Status, PublishAt
- SEO fields

========================
5) SEO (FULL)
========================
Implement SEO for public pages:
- MetaTitle, MetaDescription, MetaKeywords (optional)
- CanonicalUrl (optional)
- OG: OgTitle, OgDescription, OgImagePath
- Generate sitemap.xml including all published TR/EN routes:
  - fixed pages
  - blog posts
  - products
  - portfolio items
- robots.txt
- hreflang per page/post pairing
- JSON-LD:
  - WebSite + Organization global
  - BlogPost -> Article
  - Product -> Product (minimal)
  - Portfolio -> CreativeWork (minimal)

Add a clean 404 page.

========================
6) WORKFLOW (Draft -> Review -> Published)
========================
Implement for BlogPost/ProductItem/PortfolioItem:
- Admin can create Draft, send to Review, publish.
- Public shows only Published.
- PublishAt respected (if future, treat as not published yet).

========================
7) MEDIA (SIMPLE BUT SAFE)
========================
- Upload images to wwwroot/cdn/img/{blog|product|portfolio} based on context.
- Filename must be GUID + extension.
- Validate: only jpg/jpeg/png/webp, max size 5MB.
- Generate thumbnail on upload (e.g., 400px width) and store with `_thumb` suffix.
- Use ImageSharp (SixLabors.ImageSharp).
- Admin screens must allow selecting / uploading a featured image and for portfolio gallery.

========================
8) REDIRECT MANAGER (MIDDLEWARE)
========================
Implement middleware:
- Normalize request path
- Match active RedirectRule.OldPath
- Apply 301/302
- Prevent loops and self-redirect
Admin CRUD for RedirectRule.

========================
9) ANALYTICS / TAG MANAGER
========================
In admin, manage GA/GTM ids or scripts in SiteSettings.
Inject safely in layout (head/body positions as appropriate).

========================
10) ADMIN PANEL (TURKISH ONLY)
========================
Create Admin Area with:
- Dashboard
- Site Ayarları
- Menü Yönetimi (tree, multi-level; allow reorder via up/down buttons at minimum)
- Anasayfa İçeriği
- Hakkımızda İçeriği
- Hizmetler Sayfası İçeriği
- İletişim Sayfası İçeriği
- Referanslar Sayfası İçeriği
- SSS Sayfası İçeriği + SSS Öğeleri yönetimi
- Blog Yazıları + Blog Kategorileri
- Ürünler + Ürün Kategorileri
- Portfolyo + Portfolyo Kategorileri + Portfolyo Galeri
- İletişim Formu Mesajları (read-only list/detail)
- Yönlendirmeler (Redirect rules)

Admin UI requirements:
- Turkish labels, buttons, validation messages
- Status badges (Taslak / İnceleme / Yayında)
- Clean layout (sidebar + topbar)
- Pagination on lists
- No search required

========================
11) PUBLIC SITE (LIGHT CORPORATE THEME)
========================
Create a modern, elegant light corporate theme:
- responsive header with language switcher
- footer with settings + social links
- pages:
  - Home
  - About
  - Services (list or page sections)
  - Blog list/detail
  - Product list/detail
  - Portfolio list/detail (with gallery)
  - References
  - FAQ
  - Contact (form + info)

Ensure routing uses /{lang}/... and content is pulled by language.

========================
12) DATABASE / MIGRATIONS / SEED (MANDATORY)
========================
- EF Core migrations included
- On startup, ensure db exists and apply migrations automatically.
- Seed TR+EN:
  - Menu
  - SiteSettings
  - Fixed page content (lorem ipsum)
  - Blog categories + sample posts
  - Product categories + sample products
  - Portfolio categories + sample items with gallery
  - FAQ items

========================
13) CODE QUALITY RULES
========================
- No TODOs, no placeholders, no pseudo-code.
- Create all controllers, viewmodels, views.
- Implement Slugify helper with Turkish character normalization.
- Use AsNoTracking for public read queries.
- Validate unique slugs per language.
- Keep over-abstraction low; do not create plugin system.

========================
14) OUTPUT FORMAT
========================
Actually create the repository files. Do not provide narrative explanations.
If you must comment, keep to short code comments only.
